         <c id="ref87" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Bookplates – Personal Collections</unittitle>
               <unitid>Series IV</unitid>
            </did>
            <arrangement id="aspace_bcfc9cb246c1edaf84972c9c35cb9a98">
               <head>Arrangement</head>
               <p>This series is divided into five subseries, by collector: 1) Kołakowski Collection; 2) Krzyzanowski Collection; 3) Leszner Collection; 4) Lowenhaupt Collection of the 1964 International Ex Libris Congress in Krakow, Poland; 5) Miscellaneous.</p>
            </arrangement>
            <c id="ref88" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Kołakowski Collection</unittitle>
                  <physdescstructured coverage="whole" physdescstructuredtype="spaceoccupied">
                     <quantity>31</quantity>
                     <unittype>items</unittype>
                  </physdescstructured>
                  <container containerid="39002091385063"
                             id="aspace_4e781cb3b26b7526f2c5c957cbdbdd79"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">3</container>
                  <container id="aspace_1dea0f15849f7a962bd871cf9844865c"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_4e781cb3b26b7526f2c5c957cbdbdd79">37</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_5a78ab525c597e4643a8cfc2da8cf016">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>The Kołakowski Collection comprises five personal bookplate designs for M. B. Kołakowski, including two executed by Barylski (see also Folder 5), and one bookplate belonging to Paul Cazin.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref91" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Krzyzanowski Collection</unittitle>
                  <physdesc id="aspace_fb6ca79b211ef47ef9d4a9ee583c7047">58 bookplates; 15 carte-de-visite</physdesc>
                  <container containerid="39002091385063"
                             id="aspace_5ea3ef2c5886c8eb3241fb01d5da193d"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">3</container>
                  <container id="aspace_7a1bc5979d8b58da34534cb4b66450e0"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_5ea3ef2c5886c8eb3241fb01d5da193d">38</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_71b217636070121130df3750c66ca82a">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>The Krzyzanowski Collection comprises a total of 73 works by Kazimierz Wiszniewski, many of which are signed by the artist. The collection includes six hand-colored bookplates and Wiszniewski's own carte-de-visite.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref94" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Leszner Collection</unittitle>
                  <physdesc id="aspace_40bccd76f2d4ae5608cccdc0d18980a2">162 bookplates; 1 postcard; 2 pieces of correspondence</physdesc>
                  <container containerid="39002091385063"
                             id="aspace_7f1570677c8ff99f4877da85011aa4df"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">3</container>
                  <container id="aspace_cc391fc4b958028a23230f6d3fc2e90c"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_7f1570677c8ff99f4877da85011aa4df">39-46</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_d2650793cc71f6582164060f5f49a304">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>The Leszner Collection comprises 162 total bookplates. It includes both personal designs for Tadeusz Leszner as well as numerous examples of other private and institutional bookplate commissions. Many items include inscriptions on the verso noting artist and date of execution. See Folder 46, which also contains a postcard and two pieces of correspondence.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref97" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Lowenhaupt Collection of the 1964 International Ex Libris Congress in Krakow, Poland</unittitle>
                  <physdesc id="aspace_d5369b88b6acc969422918ace88d4dc1">60 bookplates; 14 pieces of correspondence and ephemera</physdesc>
                  <container containerid="39002091385063"
                             id="aspace_9fbd0c6c3dff2262188951be9af21e76"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">3</container>
                  <container id="aspace_934d88cee077a85bf1b68850708a3e83"
                             localtype="folder"
                             parent="aspace_9fbd0c6c3dff2262188951be9af21e76">47-48</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_13f6dd2e95d38df8988b42f30d0374fe">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>The Lowenhaupt Collection of the 1964 International Ex Libris Congress in Krakow, Poland, comprises the following: a numbered portfolio of 60 bookplates published in conjunction with the congress; nine additional congress programs (many of which were mailed to Mr. Warren Hiram Lowenhaupt by the Polish bookplate society, Musaeum Publicum a Nomine Familiae Przypkowski Vocatum, in Jedrzejow, Poland); one typed "Notice to Foreigners" from the General Consulate of the Polish People's Republic; three miscellaneous ticket stubs; and one tourist's brochure of Krakow.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
